class Solution {
    public int maximumXOR(int[] nums) {
        int result = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            result |= num;
        }
        return result;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The maximum XOR is achieved by having all bits set that are present in any of the numbers. The operation allows us to clear bits in individual numbers, effectively allowing us to achieve the XOR of the bitwise OR of all numbers. Thus, we simply OR all numbers together to get the maximum possible XOR.
